6. Garbage Collection
Python uses two mechanisms:
1.	Reference counting (primary)
2.	Generational garbage collection (secondary)
The GC divides objects into 3 generations and cleans older ones less frequently. This improves performance because long-lived objects are less likely to be garbage.
You can control GC:
import gc
gc.collect()
Interview tip:
Mention that GC handles circular references, which reference counting alone cannot. Also useful in debugging memory leaks in long-running systems.
