7. Decorators
Decorators are functions that modify the behavior of another function without changing its code.
Example:
def logger(func):
    def wrapper():
        print("Start")
        func()
        print("End")
    return wrapper
Used as:
@logger
def test():
    print("Hello")
Internally:
test = logger(test)
Use cases:
•	Logging
•	Authentication
•	Caching
Interview insight:
Decorators rely on closures and higher-order functions. Advanced usage includes decorators with arguments and class decorators.
